{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Riolu}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fighting|prevnum=446|prev=Munchlax|nextnum=448|next=Lucario|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Riolu}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Riolu\n|jname=リオル\n|jtranslit=Rioru\n|tmname=Riolu\n|ndex=447\n|sdex=115\n|u2dex=033\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=062\n|adex=279\n|abrow=222\n|obrow=264\n|opbrow=178\n|type1=Fighting\n|category=Emanation\n|height-ftin=2\'04"\n|height-m=0.7\n|weight-lbs=44.5\n|weight-kg=20.2\n|abilitylayout=2\n|ability1=Steadfast\n|ability2=Inner Focus\n|abilityd=Prankster\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Undiscovered\n|eggcycles=25\n|evtotal=1\n|evat=1\n|expyield=57\n|oldexp=72\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=75\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=riolu\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Riolu\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'リオル\'\'\' \'\'Riolu\'\') is a {{type|Fighting}} [[baby Pokémon]] introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Lucario}} when [[level]]ed up with high [[friendship]] during the [[Time|day]].\n\n==Biology==\nRiolu is a small, blue, canine Pokémon. It has black legs and torso, a blue tail, and a yellow collar. It has rounded bumps on the backs of its forepaws. It has a black "mask" and red eyes. It stands on its toes instead of its entire foot. It is sensitive to a special type of energy called [[Aura]]; however, It does not have the ability to fully use these powers, although it can still emanate these waves to communicate and sense them, albeit only in ripples. It has developed two black appendages that hang down from its head, which rise when Riolu reads or manipulates aura, a special energy that it senses. Like almost all Fighting-type Pokémon, Riolu naturally has superhuman strength, stamina, and endurance and is capable of making long journeys on foot in a short amount of time. It is a playful, energetic, and loyal Pokémon.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Cameron Riolu.png|thumb|220px|left|Riolu in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Aura Sphere Riolu]]====\nRiolu debuted in \'\'[[DP071|Pokémon Ranger and the Kidnapped Riolu! Part 1]]\'\' and \'\'[[DP072|Part 2]]\'\'. This Riolu had been trained to use {{m|Aura Sphere}} and was unnaturally strong. It was taken away from the lab by [[J\'s henchmen]] that wanted to exploit it but {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}} returned it to [[Lucario Kingdom|its kingdom]], with [[Kellyn]]\'s help. This Riolu developed a strong bond with {{Ash}}.\n\n====[[Cameron\'s Riolu]]====\nA Riolu appeared in \'\'[[BW093|Goodbye, Junior Cup - Hello Adventure!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{un|Cameron}}. It evolved into a Lucario in \'\'[[BW107|Cameron\'s Secret Weapon!]]\'\'. It tends to [[Walking Pokémon|walk outside of its Poké Ball]].\n\n====[[Korrina\'s Riolu]]====\nKorrina\'s Riolu, currently a Lucario, appeared in \'\'[[XY030|Mega Revelations!]]\'\' in a flashback.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Riolu appeared in the [[boss fantasy]] of \'\'[[DP092|A Lean Mean Team Rocket Machine!]]\'\'.\n\nA Riolu appeared in \'\'[[PK24|Meloetta\'s Moonlight Serenade]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon watching {{an|Meloetta}}\'s concert.\n\nTwo {{pkmn|Trainer}}s\' Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\', with one appearing in a flashback.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM007|That\'s Why the Litten is a Scamp!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM013|Racing to a Big Event!]]\'\', where it participated in the [[Pokémon Pancake Race]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM017|Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM021|One Journey Ends, Another Begins...]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM023|Getting the Band Back Together!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM027|A Glaring Rivalry!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM086|I Choose Paradise!]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Paradise Resort]].\n\nTwo Trainers\' Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM090|Securing the Future!]]\'\', where they joined the rest of [[Alola]] in showering {{DL|Light trio (anime)|Necrozma}} with light so it could return to its {{DL|List of Pokémon with form differences|Necrozma|true form}}.\n\nA Trainer\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[SM092|Turning the Other Mask!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP071|Riolu|Ash\'s Pokédex|Riolu, the Emanation Pokémon. When sad or scared, Riolu\'s [[aura]] becomes stronger as a way of signaling its allies.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW093|Riolu|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Riolu, the Emanation Pokémon. Riolu has the power to see and understand emotions like happiness and anger in aura waves.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Black & White\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Maylene Riolu Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Riolu in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n[[File:Riley Riolu Egg Adventures.png|thumb|left|150px|A Riolu {{pkmn|Egg}} in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Phantom Thief Pokémon 7 manga===\n{{main|Hiori\'s Riolu}}\nIn [[Phantom Thief Pokémon 7]], Hiori\'s Lucario used to be a Riolu during [[Hiori]] and {{OBP|Lily|Pokémon 7}}\'s childhoods.\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters B2 W2 ~ A New Legend ~ manga===\nA Riolu appeared in [[ANL3]], under the ownership of [[Arata]].\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl manga===\nA Riolu appeared in a flashback in [[PDP20]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PS356|Magnificent Meditite & Really Riolu I]]\'\', [[Maylene]] owns a Riolu. He is seen using {{m|Drain Punch}} against {{adv|Pearl}}\'s [[Chimler|Monferno]], who {{adv|Platinum}} borrowed in order to fight her. However, in the end, he lost to a well-placed {{m|Mach Punch}} that the girl had perfected by watching slot machines.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS382|Vexing Vespiquen & Unmanageable Mothim II]]\'\', {{adv|Diamond}} helps protect an {{pkmn|Egg}} containing Riolu from two [[Team Galactic|Galactic]]-hired thugs, and after they are defeated, it hatches and is shown to interact with its {{p|Lucario|evolved form}}. It decided to stay with [[Riley]].\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[PS423|Tackling Togekiss]]\'\'.\n\nA student\'s Riolu appeared in \'\'[[PS530|Movie Panic]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n[[Hareta]] gained a Riolu {{pkmn|Egg}} in \'\'[[DPA10|Serious Training on Iron Island!!]]\'\', which hatched into a Riolu later on. It has since evolved into a {{p|Lucario}}.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Riolu (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]===\nRiolu appears as a trophy.\n\n====Trophy information====\n\'\'"An Emanation Pokémon. It constantly emits Aura energy. When it\'s frightened or sad, this energy grows stronger and informs its companions of its situation. It\'s known for its very flexible yet surpassingly powerful body. Thanks to its strength, it can crest three mountains and cross two canyons in a single night. When it levels up, it evolves into Lucario."\'\'\n\n===\'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'===\nA Riolu appeared in \'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'.\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fighting}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=115|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=The [[aura]] that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=Its body is little yet powerful. It can crest three mountains and cross two canyons in one night.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.}}\n{{Dex/En